Short Title: Harrison's Law. (Public)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
March 24, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO ENACT HARRISON'S LAW TO REVISE THE CRIMINAL OFFENSE OF
3 HAZING AND TO PUBLISH TOTAL COMPENSATION AND POSITION
4 INFORMATION FOR CENTRAL OFFICE EMPLOYEES.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1.(a) This section shall be known and may be cited as "Harrison's Law."
7 SECTION 1.(b) G.S. 14-35 reads as rewritten:
8 "§ 14-35. Hazing; definition and punishment.
9 (a) It is unlawful for any student in attendance at any university, college, or school in this
10 State to engage in hazing, or to aid or abet any other student in the commission of this offense.
11 For the purposes of this section hazing is defined as follows: "to subject another student to
12 physical injury as part of an initiation, or as a prerequisite to membership, into any organized
13 school group, including any society, athletic team, fraternity or sorority, or other similar group."
14 Any violation of this section subsection shall constitute a Class 2 A1 misdemeanor.
15 (b) It is unlawful for any school personnel, including, but not limited to, a teacher, school
16 administrator, student teacher, school safety officer, or coach, at any university, college, or school
17 in this State to engage in hazing or to aid or abet any other person in the commission of this
18 offense. Any violation of this subsection shall constitute a Class I felony.
19 (c) For the purposes of this section, hazing is defined as subjecting a student to physical
20 or serious psychological injury as part of an initiation, or as a prerequisite to membership, into
21 any organized school group, including any society, athletic team, fraternity or sorority, or other
22 similar group."
23 SECTION 2.(a) G.S. 115C-320 reads as rewritten:
24 "§ 115C-320. Certain records open to inspection.Publication and inspection of certain
25 records.
26 (a) Each local board of education shall maintain a record of each of its employees,
27 showing the following information with respect to each employee:
28 (1) Name.
29 (2) Age.
30 (3) Date of original employment or appointment.
31 (4) The terms of any contract by which the employee is employed whether written
32 or oral, past and current, to the extent that the board has the written contract
33 or a record of the oral contract in its possession.
34 (5) Current position.
*S375-v-4*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (6) Title.
2 (7) Current salary.total compensation, as defined in sub-subdivision a. of
3 subdivision (1) of subsection (b1) of this section.
4 (8) Date and amount of each increase or decrease in salary total compensation, as
5 defined in sub-subdivision a. of subdivision (1) of subsection (b1) of this
6 section, with that local board of education.
7 (9) Date and type of each promotion, demotion, transfer, suspension, separation,
8 or other change in position classification with that local board of education.
9 (10) Date and general description of the reasons for each promotion with that local
10 board of education.
11 (11) Date and type of each dismissal, suspension, or demotion for disciplinary
12 reasons taken by the local board of education. If the disciplinary action was a
13 dismissal, a copy of the written notice of the final decision of the local board
14 education setting forth the specific acts or omissions that are the basis of the
15 dismissal.
16 (12) The office or station to which the employee is currently assigned.
17 (b) For the purposes of this section, the term "central office employees" refers to
18 superintendents, assistant superintendents, associate superintendents, directors/coordinators,
19 supervisors, finance officers, all personnel categorized as central office employees by the
20 Department of Public Instruction or the local school administrative unit, and any permanent
21 employee of the local school administrative unit or employee of a third-party contractor with the
22 local school administrative unit that is not assigned to a school campus. The term "salary"
23 includes pay, benefits, incentives, supplements, bonuses, and deferred and all other forms of
24 compensation paid by the employing entity.
25 (b1) No later than August 15, 2025, and annually thereafter, each local board of education
26 shall publish and maintain on its website all of the following information:
27 (1) For each central office employee:
28 a. Total compensation from all funding sources, including at least the
29 following:
30 1. Salary.
31 2. Reimbursements and allowances, including reimbursements
32 and allowances related to travel.
33 b. Position title.
34 c. Position description.
35 d. The date the position was created.
36 e. The department, unit, or office of the local school administrative unit
37 in which the position is located.
38 (2) The title of each central office employee position in the local school
39 administrative unit and the number of positions associated with that title.
40 (3) For each department, unit, or office of the local school administrative unit:
41 a. The number of central office employees located in that department,
42 unit, or office.
43 b. The number of central office employees for each position title.
44 (c) Subject only to rules and regulations for the safekeeping of records adopted by the
45 local board of education, every person having custody of the records shall permit them to be
46 inspected and examined and copies made by any person during regular business hours. The name
47 of a participant in the Address Confidentiality Program established pursuant to Chapter 15C of
48 the General Statutes shall not be open to inspection and shall be redacted from any record released
49 pursuant to this section. Any person who is denied access to any record for the purpose of
50 inspecting, examining or copying the record shall have a right to compel compliance with the
